message.content:
cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on training spiking neural networks using a hybrid macro/micro level backpropagation algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges of training spiking neural networks and proposes a new algorithm to improve their performance. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on image recognition tasks using the MNIST and N-MNIST datasets. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the potential of spiking neural networks for ultra-low power event-driven neuromorphic hardware. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the challenges of handling spiking discontinuities in training spiking neural networks.
